reintroduction of C. calderoni. If this is not viable, the status of the site should be re-evaluated.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c4208fc5-f62d-4697-bd45-fee6c78add16": {"__data__": {"id_": "c4208fc5-f62d-4697-bd45-fee6c78add16", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/marplasticcs-economic-briefs-thailand-case-study-net-fisheries", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "MARPLASTICCs Economic Briefs - Thailand - Case study on net fisheries", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/marplasticcs-economic-briefs-thailand-case-study-net-fisheries", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f3cb99348566e168398b961573a94991eaa05278b41867ef9595bf7402c27c62"}, "2": {"node_id": "7e9b95b1-27c2-489e-a5ec-1775fee1add8", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/marplasticcs-economic-briefs-thailand-case-study-net-fisheries", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b4e71012252d319a7f4cf10a815891ce12f78d68dd4b74df2a18dde6e2813977"}}, "hash": "26590b2177db0603749cb7265e7b311b1228de330195ece22369dca0dbdbd5b4", "text": "If this is not viable, the status of the site should be re-evaluated. Non-native species: Stone loach (Barbatula barbatula) \u00a9 OpenCage, Wikimedia Commons, License cc-by-sa-2.5 \u00a9 Ronaldo Sousa EN Trigger species: Northern iberian s