 mountain streams and springs. It contains an important population of the spring snail Iberhoratia aurorae. Several threatened fish species and diverse communities of macroinvertebrates were detected. A threatened odonate species and a near- threatened bivalve species were also found. Aquatic plants were not surveyed. \u00a9 Manuel Lopes-Lima BIOPOLIS-CIBIO/InBIO Source: data compiled by the authors with categories from IUCN Red List. Figure 4. Map of Sierra de Gredos y Candelario, with the KBA site in green and the site identified as possible KBA by M\u00e1iz-Tom\u00e9 et al. (2017) in orange.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ff6b73f9-c4bc-4da5-92fa-5d182001ac86": {"__data__": {"id_": "ff6b73f9-c4bc-4da5-92fa-5d182001ac86", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/marplasticcs-economic-briefs-thailand-case-study-net-fisheries", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "MARPLASTICCs Economic Briefs - Thailand - Case study on net fisheries", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/marplasticcs-economic-briefs-thailand-case-study-net-fisheries", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f428198af6c7aa919b00bb93d67afd33621d2d93973ea369a8943848f0eab776"}, "2": {"node_id": "06ac0c61-3582-437e-bd33-d07ce4f7ba31", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/marplasticcs-economic-briefs-thailand-case-study-net-fisheries", "Author": "International Union for Conservati