...................................................................................... I Acknowledgments ..................................................................................................... II Acronyms ................................................................................................................... III List of figures............................................................................................................. IV List of tables .............................................................................................................. IV 1 Introduction ............................................................................................................. 1 2 Methodology ............................................................................................................ 4 2.1 Documentation framework ..................................................................................... 4 2.2 Case study selection and documentation .............................................................. 5 3 International case studies ...................................................................................... 6 3.1 Medmerry managed coastal realignment .............................................................. 7 3.2 Flood-based agriculture in the upper Mekong delta floodplain ........................... 11 3.3 Maristanis integrated coastal and wetlands management .................................. 17 3.4 Sustainable aquaculture and innovative seaweed farming in Zanzibar .............. 20 4 Summary of results ............................................................................................... 25 References ................................................................................................................ 26 I Abstract English Nature-based Solutions (NbS) have gained increasing importance in tackling modern societal challenges. Case studies can be a useful tool to illustrate the value of NbS interventions. They demonstrate the elements that are essential for the successful design, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of NbS and thus enable learning from experiences in different contexts. The IUCN Global Standard for Nature-based Solutions\u1d40\u1d39 is particular suited to document the positive contributions of NbS. Based on its science-based and widely consulted criteria and indicators, the Standard helps verify NbS applications and promotes comparability as well as a coherent and consistent framework for benchmarking interventions. This supplementary report to the CCICED Special Policy Study: Value Assessment of Nature-based Solutions describes the", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ae2d448c-9512-46ad-b5e2-8b4c52619139": {"__data__": {"id_": "ae2d448c-9512-46ad-b5e2-8b4c52619139", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/using-case-studies-enhance-guidance-other-effective-area-based", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Using Case Studies to Enhance Guidance on Other Effective Area Based Conservation Measures", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/using-case-studies-enhance-guidance-other-effective-area-based", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7e22f33bea27cd9c298cdf2f5d366715e2827a80277f9a2729356527f6bb5f61"}, "3": {"node_id": "13050c79-9bd7-4dd2-8f49-82d211930c09", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/us